-- Nigeria to raise up to 350 bln naira in bonds in Q3
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Thu Jun 26, 2014 12:07PM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, June 26 (Reuters) - Nigeria will raise between 260 billion and 350 billion naira ($1.60 billion-$2.15 billion) in the third quarter by selling bonds with maturities ranging from three years to 20 years, the Debt Management Office (DMO) said on Friday.

The DMO said a new 20-year bond will be sold in July while all other issuance will be reopenings of oustanding bonds. A breakdown of planned issuance is shown in the table below.  Date of Issue  TenorAmount(bln naira) July 16, 2014   3-year  10-2010-year  45-5520-year  30-40  August 13, 2014 3-year  10-2010-year  45-5520-year  30-40  September 17, 2014  3-year  10-2010-year  45-5520-year  35-45  Total 260-350  Source: Debt Management Office